cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques (specifically LSTM networks) to analyze ADS-B flight data for detecting surveillance aircraft. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the detection of anomalies, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the use of autoencoders and neural networks falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of time series data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
